do all plants need drainage pots in the inside of the actual pot i bought a small plant and it came inside a drainage pot i took the plant out of the pot and placed it in a decorative one which does not have any drainage holes at the bottom but i heard that i have to have an inner pot with holes or a decorative pot with a hole at the bottom i do not want a drainage pot because they look ugly are they any other solutions please help keep plants in the original container or transplant to a slightly larger container place this ugly plastic container inside your decorative pot then stuff foam or plastic bags around the edges between the two pots top with spanish moss buy in a bag from craft stores or large wood chips this is how professional plant companies achieve a 'finished' look the next time yo are in a 'professional' building i e bank hospital etc take a look at the plants i worked with an interior plant company for several years hope this help Atomic Kitten Jon Secada Jennifer Lopez EastEnders One Tree Hill (TV series) Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Kodocha My Life With the Thrill Kill Kult The Shining (film) St. Elmo's Fire (film) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Pip (South Park episode) Whitney Houston W.I.T.C.H. Neighbours Crazy in Love T.A.T.u. Girls Aloud Avenue Q Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist The Outsiders (novel) The Four Tops Gothic metal Sex and the City Rich Mullins Jean Grey Mary Jane Watson Miss Saigon Music of Iran Pink (musician) Pitaten Donna Pinciotti Fancy Crane Beyonc__ Knowles Wolfrider The Lovely Bones Phoebe Buffay's songs Cher (entertainer) 2005 Kashmir earthquake Yu-Gi-Oh! anime, manga or movie only characters Mindy McCready Dead Like Me Maury Fiddler on the Roof Hollyoaks Cyndi Lauper Knots Landing Honey and Clover Smallville (Season 4) Faith (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Frankie Vaughan Free Me Cliff Richard Queen (band) Phoebe Halliwell Donna Summer Brigadoon Sin City Unreleased Madonna songs Takuya Kimura Fiona Apple Kelly Clarkson The 